<![CDATA[<div align="center" style=""><div align="center" style=""><div align="center" style=""><div align="center" style=""><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" style=""><b style=""><span style="color: rgb(0, 153, 191);">Use In-Line Edit to Update Selling Stage to Closed</span></b><font color="#0099bf" style=""><b><br><br></b></font></font></div><div align="center" style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText" style="box-sizing: border-box;">If you are updating opportunities to Closed/Booked this afternoon,&nbsp;</span><span style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><u>please use the in-line edit function to update the Selling Stage field to Closed/Booked or Closed/Lost</u></span></span></span><span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText" style="box-sizing: border-box;">&nbsp;instead of using the Sales Path to mark the stage.&nbsp;</span></font></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><img src="https://ncr--c.documentforce.com/servlet/servlet.ImageServer?id=0150g0000076Xss&amp;oid=00D700000008mDk" border="0" align="left" alt=""><br></font></span></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText" style="box-sizing: border-box;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></span></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span dir="ltr" class="uiOutputText" style="box-sizing: border-box;">There is a component error that will appear if you try to Close an opportunity using the Sales Path and we are working to resolve.&nbsp;</span><u>Using the edit function to update the opportunity will allow you to successfully Close the opportunity.</u></font></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></u></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></u></p><p style="color: rgb(8, 7, 7); box-sizing: border-box; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Thank you,</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><font color="#404040" face="Arial, sans-serif">Lori Rickards<br></font><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Salesforce Administrator<br></span><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Global Sales Operations</span></p></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
